article.headline: Arizona 78, UCLA 73
article.story: TUCSON, Ariz. -- Kyle Fogg made seven of 10 3-pointers en route to a career-high 26 points and the Arizona Wildcats rallied from 14 down in the second half to beat UCLA 78-73 on Thursday night. Fogg scored 19 in the second half, including 5 of 6 3s. His previous career best was 25 against UCLA earlier this season, and he had never made more than four 3s in a game. Arizona (15-14, 9-8 Pac-10) clinched when the Bruins' Nikola Dragovic was called for an intentional foul against Derrick Williams with 14 seconds left and the Wildcats leading 70-68. Williams, who had 12 points and 11 rebounds, sank both free throws, and Arizona got the ball out of bounds. Nic Wise made four free throws in the last 12.6 seconds to wrap up the season series sweep for the Wildcats. Michael Roll scored 21 and Dragovic 19 for the Bruins (13-16, 8-9).
